[DQR.IFRS.0126.9595] The statement [00040] - Statement - CashFlowStatement includes an inconsistent calculation. The value of the concept ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInOperatingActivities of -11,459,000 should be equal to the sum of its child components defined in the calculation linkbase. The sum of these child components is -23,554,000. The values of the addends is determined by adding the values of the child concepts with a decimal value of -3. All values in the financial statements should use the same decimal value. The values reported in the financial statement in the current reporting period of 2020-01-01 to 2020-12-31 should be complete if the financial statement is to be mathematically accurate and complete. The components of ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInOperatingActivities that should add to -11,459,000 are comprised of the following:
+ AdjustmentsForDepreciationAndAmortisationExpenseAndImpairmentLossReversalOfImpairmentLossRecognisedInProfitOrLoss2,513,000 + AdjustmentsForProvisions -63,000 + AdjustmentsForSharebasedPayments 328,000 - FinanceCostsPaidClassifiedAsOperatingActivities 1,654,000 + FinanceIncomeReceivedClassifiedAsOperatingActivities 17,000 - IncomeTaxesPaidRefundClassifiedAsOperatingActivities -1,776,000 - IncreaseDecreaseInWorkingCapital 2,280,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,095,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,095,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,095,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,095,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,096,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,096,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,096,000 + ProfitLossFromOperatingActivities -12,096,000
The addends are calculated based on the calculation linkbase defined for [00040] - Statement - CashFlowStatement. If addends are missing then the calculation tree should be amended. The rule will not add dimension components as the financial statement does not include a table. If dimensions are used on the statement then add a table to ensure that the dimensions are defined correctly.
